CatDescriptText: Mrs. Janie Crumpton, pressor, 612 Conklin Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you believe churches of any denomination receive appreciation financial help from racketeers?" answer reads: "Of course they do.  I don't think that they should, however, because churches are supposed to be against the rackets."
